heading: IEE729D SLIP ID=xxxx ALREADY EXISTS. REENTER ID KEYWORD OR 'CANCEL'
content:
Explanation

  A SLIP SET COMMAND specified a SLIP trap identifier, but another SLIP trap
  already has that identifier. In the message text:

  ID=xxxx
      The SLIP trap identifier specified on the SLIP command.

  System action

  The system waits for the operator to reply.

  Operator response

  Do one of the following:

  o Reply REPLY id,ID=xxxx to specify a new SLIP trap identifier, where xxxx
  is the identifier.

  o Reply REPLY id,CANCEL to cancel the original SLIP command.

  id is the identifier preceding the message number.

  Source

  SLIP

  Module

  IEECB905

  Routing code

  *

  Descriptor code

  5
